      "name": "Amity",
      "type": "spell",
      "img": "icons/svg/daze.svg",
      "system": {
        "description": "<p><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">The College of Friends always sends out its Factotums on nights after Amity </span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">classes. Clearing out the bars and brothels of their drunken apprentices is </span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">tiring work. Use of this Spell causes the target to Test their Luck (or Skill </span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">for Enemies) or become very friendly towards the wizard, as though they </span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">were an old friend. They won&rsquo;t act irrationally, though, and if they were </span><span dir=\"ltr\" role=\"presentation\">already a bit of a boor this might not change much.</span></p>",
